{"questionId":"6009","questionHtml":"<p>Determine <em>P</em>, to the correct number of significant figures including its unit.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1</em></strong></p>\n<p>Evidence of finding gradient using two points on the line at least 10 cm apart</p>\n<p>Gradient found in range: 115–135 <strong><em>or </em></strong>1.15–1.35</p>\n<p>Using <em>P</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4\\pi }}{{{K^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>K</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;to get value between 6.9 × 10<sup>–4</sup> and 9.5 × 10<sup>–4</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>W<strong>»</strong>&nbsp;and POT correct</p>\n<p>Correct unit, W <strong>and </strong>answer to 1, 2 or 3 significant figures</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2</em></strong></p>\n<p>Finds <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"I\\left( {\\frac{1}{{{y^2}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>I</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> from use of one point (<em>x </em>and <em>y</em>) on the line with <em>x</em> &gt; 6 cm&nbsp;and <em>C</em> from(b)(i)to use in <em>I</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{P}{{4\\pi {{(C + x)}^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>P</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n            <mi>C</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{\\sqrt I }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;<em>Kx</em>&nbsp;+&nbsp;<em>KC</em></p>\n<p>Correct re-arrangementto get <em>P </em>between 6.9 × 10<sup>–4</sup> and 9.5 × 10<sup>–4</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>W<strong>»</strong> and POT correct</p>\n<p>Correct unit, W <strong>and</strong>&nbsp;answer to 1, 2 or 3 significant figures</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award </em><strong><em>[3 max] </em></strong><em>for an answer between 6.9 W and 9.5 W (POT penalized in 3rd marking point)</em></p>\n<p><em>Alternative 2 is worth </em><strong><em>[3 max]</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6009","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.2b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine P, to the correct number of significant figures including its unit.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.1 – Measurements in physics","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}